args: Thanks so much for bringing me\nall the way up here, Cleo.
Of course. I was just thinking it was time\nfor another foraging trip anyway.
It's not always easy to get this far away\nfrom the castle, is it?
Well I can't let this go to waste.\nTime to break out the sketch pad!
Hmm? Are you all right, Fleur?\nThe color has gone from your cheeks.
Has it? Weird. I feel completely fine!
I'm gonna go over there and sketch.\nSee ya in a bit!
Maybe I'm worrying for no reason...\nRegardless, I should go look for edibles.
Goodness, it's past midday already.\nWe should think about heading back.
Have you finished your sketches, Fleur?
Sure have! I'm at a good stopping point\nright now, so...um...
Uuuurgh... I feel dizzy...\nThe world's going all spinny...
My tummy hurts... I feel gross.
Nuh uh. I haven't eaten all day.
I was so focused on my art,\nI didn't even think about food.

Look, I know it might seem weird, but I
promise I can whip these fiends up into a
dish that will have you drooling all over
the forest floor. DROOLING.
And there we have it... Fiendmeat\nmiso porridge, packed full of all the\nmedicinal herbs a girl could need!
When Pecorine collapsed, the porridge\nwe made got her back on her feet.
Sorry, friend. Looks like this isn't\ngoing to be your lucky day.
Here, Fleur. I made you some healthy\nfiendmeat porridge. Can you eat?
I'm glad you like it. Can you eat more?
Are you all right, Fleur? What's wrong?
Even with my tummy hurting,\nI can totally snarf it down!
Porridge is the best thing when you're \neating for the first time after a long fast.
I'm sure your stomach was hurting from\nhunger, but make sure to eat slowly\nso you don't shock your system.
Hee hee! I feel tons better now.
Fiendmeat restores the body's mana,\nand the herbs I mixed in are full of\nadditional nutrients.
It's the perfect thing to get a person\nback on their feet.
Thank you, Fleur. Er, but if I may ask,\nhow long HAD it been since you last ate?
Hmm. Well, I spent all yesterday painting\nin my room, and the day before that I was\npainting in my room, sooo...I dunno?
It sounds like you didn't eat anything\nfor two whole days.
Fleur, I understand how easy it is to get\nlost in something you're passionate about,\nbut you have to take care of yourself.
A growing girl like yourself\nneeds proper nutrition.
So, um, does this mean you won't\ntake me out to sketch again?
Of course it doesn't. So long as\nyou're healthy about it, we can\ndo this whenever you like.
But you must promise to eat properly!
If you don't take care of yourself, you won't\nbe able to keep doing things you enjoy.
Then I'll eat tons so I can grow up\nbig and strong!
In that case, would you like seconds?
